The paper deals with the problem of counting sparse motifs in massive graphs observed in a stream, which is a common problem in several areas of computer science such as data structures (cs.DS), social networks (cs.SI), system and database management (cs.SD, cs.DB), and computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper presents a novel technique for approximate counting of sparse motifs that requires a fixed amount of memory and a single pass on the data, which is of interest to researchers in all of these sub-categories.
